1
00:00:16,520 --> 00:00:18,840
CLARA: One day, you meet the Doctor.

2
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:22,640
And of course, it's the best day ever.

3
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:25,840
It's just the best day of your life.

4
00:00:27,520 --> 00:00:30,240
Because... Because he's brilliant

5
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:32,240
and he's funny and mad.

6
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:35,080
And best of all, he really needs you.

7
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:36,800
The trick is

8
00:00:37,160 --> 00:00:38,800
don't fall in love.

9
00:00:39,560 --> 00:00:42,040
I do that trick quite a lot,
sometimes twice a day.

10
00:00:44,160 --> 00:00:45,960
And once you start running,

11
00:00:46,680 --> 00:00:48,080
you start to forget,

12
00:00:48,760 --> 00:00:50,320
slowly.

13
00:00:50,480 --> 00:00:52,000
After a while,

14
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:54,960
you just stop asking.

15
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:01,240
Who are you?

16
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:02,800
Where are you from?

17
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:06,440
What set you on your way
and where are you going?

18
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:09,040
Oh.

19
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:11,320
And what is your name?

20
00:01:14,760 --> 00:01:16,360
You get used to not knowing.

21
00:01:17,040 --> 00:01:18,800
I thought I never would.

22
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:20,920
I was wrong.

23
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:31,840
I know who he is.

24
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:34,640
I know how he began
and I know where he's going.

25
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:37,880
I learnt the truth about the Doctor
and his greatest secret.

26
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:42,120
The day we went to Trenzalore.

27
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:54,240
DOCTOR: From the beginning,
she was impossible.

28
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:57,840
The impossible girl.

29
00:01:59,080 --> 00:02:03,240
I met her in the Dalek Asylum.
Never saw her face and she died.

30
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:07,000
I met her again in Victorian London

31
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:09,080
and she died.

32
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:13,520
Saved my life both times
by giving her own.

33
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:16,200
But now she's back.

34
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:21,280
And we're running together
and she's perfect.

35
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:23,120
Perfect in every way for me,

36
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:25,200
except she can't remember
that we ever met.

37
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:28,720
Clara.

38
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:32,560
My Clara.

39
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,880
Always brave,

40
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:36,560
always funny,

41
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:40,160
always exactly what I need.

42
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:41,960
Perfect.

43
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,680
Too perfect.

44
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:48,880
You get used to not knowing.

45
00:02:50,160 --> 00:02:51,800
I thought I never would.

46
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:54,160
I was wrong.

47
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:11,800
I know who Clara Oswald is.

48
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,320
I know how she came to be in my life

49
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,720
and I know what she will always mean.

50
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:19,240
I found out

51
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:22,440
the day we went to Trenzalore.

